<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Rachid Youven Zeghlache</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/</link><description>Recent content on Rachid Youven Zeghlache</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 15 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://youvenzful.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>From YouTube to Blog Post: How I Built a Self-Maintaining Website</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/blog/2026-02-15-self-maintaining-website/</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://youvenzful.github.io/blog/2026-02-15-self-maintaining-website/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this post I walk through the three automation pipelines that keep this website up to date without any manual intervention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="tldr"&gt;TL;DR&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A daily GitHub Actions cron job fetches my latest YouTube video&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Downloads the transcript using &lt;code&gt;youtube-transcript-api&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sends it to Claude (&lt;code&gt;claude-sonnet-4-20250514&lt;/code&gt;) to generate a structured blog post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commits the Markdown file and triggers a Hugo rebuild&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="key-takeaways"&gt;Key Takeaways&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The whole process takes about 60 seconds from video publish to draft post&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Claude prompt is the most important part — iteration matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Always diff before commit to avoid unnecessary rebuilds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id="the-pipeline"&gt;The Pipeline&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="step-1-detect-new-video"&gt;Step 1: Detect new video&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f7f7f7;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#cf222e"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#24292e"&gt;yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#24292e"&gt;requests&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#cf222e"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#6639ba"&gt;get_latest_video&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;api_key&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; channel_id&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; url &lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;https://www.googleapis.com/youtube/v3/search&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; params &lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; api_key&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;channelId&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; channel_id&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;order&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;date&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;part&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;snippet&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;maxResults&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; r &lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; requests&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;get&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;url&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; params&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;params&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;json&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#cf222e"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; r&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0a3069"&gt;&amp;#34;items&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;][&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#0550ae"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#1f2328"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="step-2-generate-blog-post-with-claude"&gt;Step 2: Generate blog post with Claude&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Claude API call uses a structured prompt that ensures the output
includes all required frontmatter fields and a consistent article structure.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>GenomeInterp</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/projects/genomeinterp/</link><pubDate>Sat, 01 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://youvenzful.github.io/projects/genomeinterp/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview"&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GenomeInterp&lt;/strong&gt; is a PyTorch framework for training and interpreting neural networks that predict the regulatory effects of genomic variants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="features"&gt;Features&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention-based model architecture for sequence-to-function mapping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built-in saliency map and SHAP-based explanation tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benchmarked on the ENCODE and GTEx datasets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="installation"&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f7f7f7;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install genomeinterp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="citation"&gt;Citation&lt;/h2&gt;
